{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LiteLLM is an open-source proxy that sits between your application code and LLM provider APIs. Instead of each service embedding raw provider API keys and SDK-specific code, all services call the proxy over a standard OpenAI-compatible interface. The proxy handles credential management, model routing, fallback chains, rate limiting, budget enforcement, and logging centrally. This separation lets you change providers, add fallbacks, or rotate keys without touching application code."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "LiteLLM proxy architecture: clients send to proxy, proxy routes to Anthropic/Bedrock/Vertex/OpenAI"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why a Proxy Layer"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Without a proxy, every service that calls Claude embeds provider credentials directly and must implement fallback, retry, and logging independently. The proxy centralizes these concerns:"
          }
        ]
