      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Installation and Basic Setup"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Install LiteLLM with proxy extras\npip install 'litellm[proxy]'\n\n# Or with Docker (recommended for production)\ndocker pull ghcr.io/berriai/litellm:main-latest\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Create a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "litellm_config.yaml",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to define which models the proxy exposes:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# litellm_config.yaml\nmodel_list:\n  # Primary: Anthropic direct API\n  - model_name: claude-opus\n    litellm_params:\n      model: claude-opus-4-8\n      api_key: os.environ/ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n\n  # Fallback: Bedrock\n  - model_name: claude-opus\n    litellm_params:\n      model: bedrock/anthropic.claude-opus-4-8\n      aws_region_name: us-east-1\n\n  # Sonnet for general tasks\n  - model_name: claude-sonnet\n    litellm_params:\n      model: claude-sonnet-4-6\n      api_key: os.environ/ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n\n  # Haiku for cheap tasks\n  - model_name: claude-haiku\n    litellm_params:\n      model: claude-haiku-4-5\n      api_key: os.environ/ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n\nrouter_settings:\n  routing_strategy: latency-based-routing\n  num_retries: 3\n  retry_after: 5\n\nlitellm_settings:\n  success_callback: [\"langfuse\"]  # optional observability\n  drop_params: true\n\ngeneral_settings:\n  master_key: os.environ/LITELLM_MASTER_KEY  # admin key\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Start the proxy\nlitellm --config litellm_config.yaml --port 4000\n\n# Or with Docker\ndocker run -e ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=$ANTHROPIC_API_KEY \\\n           -e LITELLM_MASTER_KEY=$LITELLM_MASTER_KEY \\\n           -v $(pwd)/litellm_config.yaml:/app/config.yaml \\\n           -p 4000:4000 \\\n           ghcr.io/berriai/litellm:main-latest \\\n           --config /app/config.yaml\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Calling the Proxy From Application Code"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The proxy exposes an OpenAI-compatible API. Any OpenAI SDK client works without modification, just pointing to the proxy URL:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from openai import OpenAI  # Standard OpenAI SDK \u2014 no LiteLLM SDK needed in the client\n\n# Point at the proxy instead of OpenAI\nclient = OpenAI(\n    base_url=\"http://localhost:4000\",\n    api_key=\"sk-virtual-key-for-team-a\",  # virtual key, not real Anthropic key\n)\n\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"claude-opus\",   # model name as defined in litellm_config.yaml\n    max_tokens=1024,\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Explain transformer attention.\"}],\n)\nprint(response.choices[0].message.content)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You can also use the Anthropic SDK by overriding the base URL:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\n# Point the Anthropic SDK at the LiteLLM proxy\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic(\n    base_url=\"http://localhost:4000\",\n    api_key=\"sk-virtual-key-for-team-a\",\n)\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-opus\",\n    max_tokens=512,\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello\"}],\n)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Virtual API Key Management"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Virtual keys allow you to give teams or services individual keys that the proxy maps to real provider credentials. You control budgets, rate limits, and access per virtual key without exposing real API keys:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Create a virtual key for team-a with a $100/month budget\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:4000/key/generate \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $LITELLM_MASTER_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"team_id\": \"team-a\",\n    \"max_budget\": 100,\n    \"budget_duration\": \"30d\",\n    \"tpm_limit\": 100000,\n    \"rpm_limit\": 500,\n    \"models\": [\"claude-sonnet\", \"claude-haiku\"],\n    \"metadata\": {\"owner\": \"alice@example.com\"}\n  }'\n# Returns: {\"key\": \"sk-abc123...\", \"expires\": null, \"max_budget\": 100, ...}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits of virtual keys:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Key rotation without code changes",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Rotate the real Anthropic API key in the proxy config; all virtual keys continue working."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Per-team budget enforcement",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": The proxy rejects requests when a virtual key exceeds its budget \u2014 no runaway cost from a single team."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Model access control",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Restrict a virtual key to "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "claude-haiku",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " only, preventing a team from accidentally calling "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "claude-opus",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Auditability",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": All usage is logged per virtual key, enabling per-team cost attribution without aggregating from multiple services."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fallback Configuration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LiteLLM routes to the next provider in a model group when the primary fails. Configure fallback chains to handle provider outages and rate limit spikes:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# litellm_config.yaml \u2014 fallback chain example\nmodel_list:\n  - model_name: claude-primary\n    litellm_params:\n      model: claude-opus-4-8\n      api_key: os.environ/ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n\n  - model_name: claude-bedrock-fallback\n    litellm_params:\n      model: bedrock/anthropic.claude-opus-4-8\n      aws_access_key_id: os.environ/AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID\n      aws_secret_access_key: os.environ/AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY\n      aws_region_name: us-east-1\n\n  - model_name: claude-vertex-fallback\n    litellm_params:\n      model: vertex_ai/claude-opus-4-8@20251101\n      vertex_project: my-gcp-project\n      vertex_location: us-central1\n\nrouter_settings:\n  fallbacks:\n    - {\"claude-primary\": [\"claude-bedrock-fallback\", \"claude-vertex-fallback\"]}\n  context_window_fallbacks:\n    - {\"claude-primary\": [\"claude-vertex-fallback\"]}\n  num_retries: 2\n  timeout: 30\n  retry_policy:\n    AuthenticationErrorRetries: 0   # don't retry auth errors\n    RateLimitErrorRetries: 3\n    TimeoutErrorRetries: 2\n    ContentPolicyViolationErrorRetries: 0\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Testing Fallback Behavior"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# LiteLLM SDK can test fallbacks directly (useful in CI)\nimport litellm\n\nresponse = litellm.completion(\n    model=\"claude-primary\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"test\"}],\n    fallbacks=[\"claude-bedrock-fallback\", \"claude-vertex-fallback\"],\n    num_retries=2,\n    timeout=10,\n)\nprint(f\"Served by: {response._hidden_params.get('model_id')}\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Budget and Rate Limit Enforcement"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# litellm_config.yaml \u2014 global budget controls\ngeneral_settings:\n  max_budget: 500           # global $500/month hard cap across all keys\n  budget_duration: \"30d\"\n\nlitellm_settings:\n  max_budget: 500\n  budget_duration: \"30d\"\n  alerting:\n    - slack\n  alerting_threshold: 400  # alert when spend hits $400\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a virtual key hits its budget limit, the proxy returns HTTP 429 with a clear budget-exceeded message before the request reaches the provider. This prevents surprise bills from loops or runaway agents."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Request Logging and Observability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LiteLLM can forward request/response data to observability platforms. Configure callbacks in "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "litellm_settings",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ":"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "litellm_settings:\n  success_callback:\n    - langfuse        # LLM-specific tracing\n    - datadog         # APM metrics\n    - s3              # raw log archive\n  failure_callback:\n    - sentry          # error tracking\n  service_callback:\n    - prometheus      # token/cost metrics\n\n# Environment variables for each callback\n# LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY, LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY\n# DD_API_KEY\n# AWS_S3_LOG_BUCKET\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Without callback config, the proxy logs to stdout in JSON format. Parse that stream into your existing log aggregation pipeline (Datadog, CloudWatch, Elastic) for a lightweight alternative to managed callbacks."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deploying to Production"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For production, run the proxy with a persistent database for key storage and a Redis cache for rate limiting across replicas:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# docker-compose.yml\nversion: \"3.8\"\nservices:\n  litellm:\n    image: ghcr.io/berriai/litellm:main-latest\n    command: --config /app/config.yaml --detailed_debug\n    ports:\n      - \"4000:4000\"\n    environment:\n      ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${ANTHROPIC_API_KEY}\n      LITELLM_MASTER_KEY: ${LITELLM_MASTER_KEY}\n      DATABASE_URL: postgresql://postgres:password@postgres:5432/litellm\n      REDIS_URL: redis://redis:6379\n    volumes:\n      - ./litellm_config.yaml:/app/config.yaml\n    depends_on:\n      - postgres\n      - redis\n\n  postgres:\n    image: postgres:15\n    environment:\n      POSTGRES_DB: litellm\n      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: password\n\n  redis:\n    image: redis:7-alpine\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to Use LiteLLM vs Direct SDK"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Factor"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
