      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LiteLLM proxy centralizes API key management, provider routing, fallback chains, and budget enforcement for organizations running multiple services against Claude. Clients use virtual keys over an OpenAI-compatible interface; the proxy holds real provider credentials and applies routing logic transparently. Configure fallbacks in YAML to survive provider outages without code changes. Use virtual key budgets to enforce per-team spending limits before requests reach the provider. Run the proxy with Postgres and Redis for production-grade persistence and distributed rate limiting."
          }
